{
  "stem": "19198.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But since I was the only Jew of-- of my age in the Eberbach, I would go to a neighboring town, even smaller than-- than Eberbach, to meet, where there were about three or four Jews of roughly my age.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So on my commuter's ticket, I could-- I could take the train to that town, which was about halfway between Eberbach and Heidelberg, and whenever I went there, I took my-- my camera.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because that gave me reason to also carry a heavy tripod that folded up to about this length and had a very heavy metal head, so that if I would be in any way attacked, at least I would have a chance at defending myself.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I also knew that that would have relatively little meaning, because the Nazis would never attack one on one.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Would always be a whole group against one.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Your train pass.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Did-- did the Jews have different train passes than non-Jews?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, certainly not at that time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And whether they did in the-- in-- in later times, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, the-- the train-- the-- the commuter ticket itself was-- had a picture identification, but-- but I do not remember that that had any mark for identifying me as a Jew.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The decision to leave the country came with the opportunity to leave the country.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In that I think I am unique.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I am one of only five people who had the same experience.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "After graduating from high school and passing the Abitur examination, I started studying at the [NON-ENGLISH], which was the liberal rabbinical seminary in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
